<HEAD>Forbes 400 List of Wealthiest Americans</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Forbest Richest, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is Forbes magazine's 1989 list of the 400
richest Americans in descending order of wealth, showing estimated
fortune in millions, residence, source of wealth and age.
   1, John Werner Kluge, $5,200, Charlottesville, Va., Metromedia,
75.
   2, Warren Edward Buffett, $4,200, Omaha, Neb., stock market, 59.
   3, Sumner Murray Redstone, $2,880, Newton Centre, Mass., movie
theaters, 66.
   4, Ted Arison, $2,860, Miami Beach, Fla., cruise ships, 65.
   5, Ronald Owen Perelman, $2,750, New York City, leveraged
buyouts, 46.
   6, Donald Edward Newhouse, $2,600, New York City, publishing, 60.
   6, Samuel Irving Newhouse Jr., $2,600, New York City,
publishing, 61.
   8, Barbara Cox Anthony, $2,500, Honolulu, inheritance (Cox
Enterprises), 66.
   8, Anne Cox Chambers, $2,500, Atlanta, inheritance (Cox
Enterprises), 69.
   8, Henry Ross Perot, $2,500, Dallas, electronic data management,
59.
   11, Robert Alan Pritzker, $2,350, Chicago, financier, 63.
   11, Jay Arthur Pritzker, $2,350, Chicago, financier, 67.
   13, A. Alfred Taubman, $2,150, Bloomfield Hills, Mich., real
estate, 65.
   13, Lester Crown, $2,150, Wilmette, Ill., inheritance, 64.
   15, Edgar Miles Bronfman, $2,000, New York City, Seagram Co., 60.
   15, Leslie Herbert Wexner, $2,000, Columbus, Ohio, The Limited
Inc., 52.
   17, Harold Clark Simmons, $1,900, Dallas, investments, 58.
   17, David Packard, $1,900, Los Altos Hills, Calif.,
Hewlett-Packard, 77.
   19, Donald Leroy Bren, $1,850, Newport Beach, Calif., real
estate, 57.
   20, S. Robson Walton, $1,800, Bentonville, Ark., inheritance
(Wal-Mart Stores), 45.
   20, Sam Moore Walton, $1,800, Bentonville, Ark., Wal-Mart
Stores, 71.
   20, Alice L. Walton, $1,800, Rogers, Ark., inheritance (Wal-Mart
Stores), 40.
   20, John T. Walton, $1,800, San Diego, inheritance (Wal-Mart
Stores), 44.
   20, Jim C. Walton, $1,800, Bentonville, Ark., inheritance
(Wal-Mart Stores), 41.
   25, Robert Edward (Ted) Turner III, $1,760, Roswell, Ga., Turner
Broadcasting System, 50.
   26, Samuel Jayson LeFrak, $1,700, New York City, real estate, 71.
   26, Henry Lea Hillman, $1,700, Pittsburgh, industrialist, 70.
   26, Marvin Harold Davis, $1,700, Beverly Hills, Calif., oil, 64.
   26, Keith Rupert Murdoch, $1,700, New York City, publishing, 58.
   26, David Hamilton Koch, $1,700, New York City, inheritance, 49.
   26, Charles de Ganahl Koch, $1,700, Wichita, Kan., inheritance,
53.
   26, Donald John Trump, $1,700, New York City, real estate, 43.
   26, Harry Brakmann Helmsley, $1,700, New York City, real estate,
80.
   26, Charles F. Feeney, $1,700, London, Duty Free Shoppers, 58.
   35, Forrest Edward Mars Sr., $1,500, Las Vegas, candy, 80s.
   35, Forrest Edward Mars Jr., $1,500, McLean, Va., candy, 58.
   35, Jacqueline Mars Vogel, $1,500, Bedminster, N.J., candy, 50.
   35, John Franklyn Mars, $1,500, Arlington, Va., candy, 54.
   35, August Anheuser Busch Jr., $1,500, St. Louis,
Anheuser-Busch, deceased.
   35, Leonard Norman Stern, $1,500, New York City, pet supplies,
51.
   41, Robert Muse Bass, $1,440, Fort Worth, Tex., oil, 41.
   42, Walter Hubert Annenberg, $1,400, Wynnewood, Pa., publishing,
81.
   42, Edward John DeBartolo, $1,400, Boardman, Ohio, shopping
centers, 80.
   42, Ray Lee Hunt $1,400, Dallas, inheritance, 46.
   42, Roger Milliken, $1,400, Spartanburg, S.C., textiles, 73.
   46, Laurence Allan Tisch, $1,350, New York City, Loews Corp., 66.
   46, Preston Robert Tisch, $1,350, New York City, Loews Corp., 63.
   48, Ewing Marion Kauffman, $1,300, Mission Hills, Kan., Marion
Laboratories, 73.
   48, Kirk Kerkorian, $1,300, Beverly Hills, Calif., investments,
72.
   50, Michael Robert Milken, $1,270, Encino, Calif., financier,
43.
